-- MasterCard quarterly profit rises 14 pct
-- By Tanya Agrawal in Bangalore
-- Thu May 01, 2014 07:40AM EDT
-- None



May 1 (Reuters) - MasterCard Inc <MA.N>, the world's second-largest debit and credit card company, posted a 14 percent rise in quarterly profit as more customers used cards to shop.

The company's net income rose to $870 million, or 73 cents per share, for the first quarter ended March 31, from $766 million, or 62 cents per share, a year earlier. [ID:nBw7SPncYa]